The White House is deeply concerned about the escalating violence in Yemen and the resulting deaths of civilians. They specifically mention the attacks that killed an ambulance driver, a journalist, and civilians in various parts of Yemen. The United States takes these reports of civilian deaths seriously and calls on all sides of the conflict to avoid harm to civilians and comply with international humanitarian law. They also emphasize the importance of ensuring the safety, security, and freedom of movement of humanitarian personnel in Yemen. The statement expresses concern about the violence in Taiz and the need to allow the delivery of assistance to all Yemenis in need. The United States urges all parties to cooperate with the United Nations in reaching a ceasefire and resuming peace talks to find a durable solution to the crisis in Yemen.